  "texts": [
    "Entering a noisy room full of loud voices in conversation, along with unknown and unknowable furniture arrangements, food when provided is generally laid out with the instructions to \"help yourself\".",
    "These words generally strike fear for Ben, who could not attempt to identify and distinguish food items, plates and cutlery, nor to make a selection to satisfy as lunch.",
    "Ben would also generally appreciate a chair when eating it frees up a hand.",
    "Yet this may be a luxury not easily attained.",
    "Priscila recognises the distress these events can cause and without question organises a heaped plate with Ben's preferred items and manoeuvres him to sit upon a chair near people he will be able to engage with."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}